title: Warren Hills' Dani Profita is lehighvalleylive Field Hockey Player of the Week
text:
Dani Profita (lehighvalleylive.com file photo) 
Profita, a junior forward, tallied five goals and two assists in the Blue Streaks' 3-0 week. 
She had two goals in a 4-0 triumph over Montgomery, recorded a hat trick and an assist in a 7-0 win over Phillipsburg, and notched an assist and also scored the decisive penalty stroke in a 2-1 overtime win over Voorhees in a Hunterdon/Warren/Sussex semifinal. 
Profita had 22 goals and 11 assists through 14 games this season. 
Honorable mention :Fr. F Ellie McIntyre , Easton; Jr. M Anissa Abboud , Liberty; So. M Olivia Sahaydak , Liberty; Sr. F Meghan Hemingway , Northampton; Jr. F Emme Lentine , Bangor; Jr. M Cheyenne Ott , Bangor; Jr. F Mayv Clune , Moravian Academy; Devon Nothstein , Northwestern; So. F Meghan Reese , Southern Lehigh; Jr. F Molly Gorczyca , Hackettstown; Sr. F Kayli Yeisley , Hackettstown.
